<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF893951EBD2C5F8FBEC586D" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF893951EBD2C5F8FEAA59D3" blockId="39.[227,341,715,741]" box="[227,341,715,741]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="5A24A609FF893951EBD2C5F8FEAA59D3" bold="true" box="[227,341,715,741]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF893951EBD2C5F8FEAA59D3" bold="true" box="[227,341,715,741]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF893951EBD2C5C9FBEC586D" blockId="39.[227,1436,762,860]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
The otoliths of “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF893951EA94C5C9FE3F5822" box="[421,448,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">C.</emphasis>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF893951EAE4C5C9FDC95822" box="[469,566,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">prolatus</emphasis>
are characterized by a relatively elongate shape, a wide sulcus, an ostium opening widely to the antero-dorsal rim, and a small dorsal depression. The combination of these characters may point to an extinct taxon within the family 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF893951E8A0C472FBF0586D" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1856" box="[913,1039,833,859]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Congridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anguilliformes" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Congridae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
